There is a shooting requirement which is not designed to be challenging but is intended to ensure that each CCDW holder is able to safely control and fire their weapon by hitting only their intended target. Each class participant should bring a good quality handgun, either a revolver or semi-automatic, with 50 rounds of ammunition of the correct caliber. Participants are also required to bring eye and ear protection and a basic gun cleaning kit. Participants that do not bring their own eye & ear protection will be required to purchase those things at the class. For other questions concerning eligibility or anything not covered in the FAQ below please email the primary course instructor at REDACTED. Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?- Must be a legal Kentucky Resident and bring your valid Driver's License or State Issued ID to the class.- Must be no less than 21 years of age- Email REDACTED with other questions concerning eligibility What are my transport/parking options getting to the event?- Free parking available at location. What must I bring to the event?- Must bring valid driver's license or state issued ID- Must bring a functioning quality handgun (revolver or semi-automatic)- Must bring 50 rounds of ammunition for your handgun of the correct caliber- Must bring eye and ear protection (you will be required to purchase if not with you)- Must bring a basic cleaning kit- Must wear closed-toe shoes and dress appropriately for weather (range is outside, class is indoors).- If you have dietary restrictions you are welcome to bring your own lunch. (A refrigerator is not available.) Can I shoot re-loaded ammunition?- No. All ammunition used must be good quality and factory loaded. Where can I contact the organizer with any questions?- All questions should go to David Meek at REDACTED   What is the refund policy?- The $25 registration fee is non-refundable. The $60 balance is due in cash upon arrival the day of class and is not refundable if you do not pass the course. If you fail you may* be allowed to re-take the course at a reduced rate. That is up to the discretion of LouKyCCDW.com and the primary instructor David Meek.  Will LouKyCCDW.com teach a private class?- Yes. Private classes require a minimum number of participants.
